    <segment id="1" parent="28" relname="span">John Bailar asks again</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="1" relname="background"> [thanks for the persistence, John!]</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="44" relname="span"> what is the
object of science studies. </segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="5" relname="preparation">
Well. </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="29" relname="span">
I certainly can&apos;t talk for ANYone else,</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="30" relname="span"> but I can talk for myself well
enough.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="43" relname="span"> My goals are at least three in nature.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="33" relname="span">

1. To accomplish something substantive in theoretical physics.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="32" relname="span"> I&apos;ve been
partnered with a theoretical physicist since &apos;73,</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="9" relname="elaboration"> and we&apos;ve done some neat
things together that we couldn&apos;t have done apart.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="34" relname="span"> [My greatest
accomplishment in our personal friendship was to finally convince him that
particles were a waste of his talent, and that general relativity was
&apos;where it was at&apos;!</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="11" relname="background"> Sorry, S. Traweek!]</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="35" relname="span">

2. To understand something substantive about how science, in particular,
physics and cosmology, actually work.</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="36" relname="span"> This is a purely intellectual goal,
for which I
apologize to absolutely no one.</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="15" relname="elaboration"> Knowledge is its own reward.</segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="42" relname="span">

3. To attempt to improve science education</segment>
    <segment id="21" parent="38" relname="span"> [assuming that my presence and
knowledge would be contributory in and of themselves--</segment>
    <segment id="20" parent="18" relname="concession">arrogant perhaps,</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="37" relname="span"> but
there you have it],</segment>
    <segment id="19" parent="41" relname="span"> by designing and teaching physical science courses for
teacher-candidates in the Ed School.</segment>
    <segment id="22" parent="39" relname="conjunction"> I&apos;ve done this for about 5 years now.</segment>
    <segment id="23" parent="39" relname="conjunction">
It&apos;s extremely hard. </segment>
    <segment id="24" parent="40" relname="span">But I&apos;ve convinced myself it&apos;s worth it.</segment>
    <segment id="25" parent="24" relname="elaboration"> We&apos;ll see.</segment>
    <segment id="26" parent="47" relname="span">

So that&apos;s what *I* want to do.</segment>
    <segment id="27" parent="26" relname="elaboration"> Don&apos;t know about anyone else.</segment>
